        "timestamp": 1727199578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have anything like this?</p>",
        "id": 472543669,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1727199582
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i don't get what you mean? <code>List.Pairwise</code> is independent of <code>R a a</code> for <code>a</code> in the list?</p>",
        "id": 472544091,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1727199735
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, that's the thing. In a reflexive relation, you do have <code>R a a</code>, so you don't need the <code>a ≠ b</code> assumption.</p>",
        "id": 472544211,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1727199789
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would guess you can get there via <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Pairwise.set_pairwise#doc\">docs#List.Pairwise.set_pairwise</a></p>",
        "id": 472555458,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727204158
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>combined with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Set/Pairwise/Basic.html#Set.Pairwise.of_refl\">Set.Pairwise.of_refl</a>, that should get you there</p>",
